{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, interleukin-6 has been linked to the pathogenesis of AD, while tumor necrosis factor-α has been proposed as a potent therapeutic target for AD.",
    "Lutein, a carotenoid also found in Choerospondias axillas, is also found as a protective intervention.",
    "This finding corroborates prior reports that demonstrated an inverse association between lutein intake and dementia occurrence 62.",
    "Furthermore, increased lutein intake has been associated with lower levels of AD neuropathology postmortem 63.",
    "Overall, Choerospondias axillaris and other yellow-pigmented fruits may act as protectors by reducing the levels of proinflammatory cytokines crucially implicated in AD."
  ]
}